text.section:
A county board shall reimburse the Department of Juvenile Services the amount of the basic cost calculated under subsection (a) of this section for each child who was domiciled in the county prior to the placement if the child:
Is committed to the Department of Juvenile Services and is in a program at a facility or a residential facility;
Is not in detention or awaiting placement after disposition;
Does not meet the criteria for shared State and local payment of educational costs as provided in §§ 8-406 and 8-415 of this article; and
Was included in the full-time equivalent enrollment of the county as calculated under § 5-202 of this article.
